{"word":"οὖρον 2","slug":"οὖρον 2","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n76018\" key=\"ou)=ron2\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">οὖρον</orth> (B), <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">τό</gen>, <sense id=\"n76018.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">limit, range</tr_>, <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">δίσκου οὖρα</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:23:431\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">23.431</biblScope></bibl></cit>, cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">δίσκουρα; ὅσσον τ᾽ ἐπὶ οὖρα πέλονται ἡμιόνων, αἱ γάρ τε βοῶν προφερέστεραί εἰσιν ἑλκέμεναι νειοῖο βαθείης πηκτὸν ἄροτρον</foreign> the <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">range</tr_> of mules, i.e. the breadth of land ploughed in a day by mules, the length of the furrow being fixed, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:10:351\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">10.351</biblScope> </bibl>: so in sg., <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ὅσσον τ᾽ ἐν νειῷ οὖρον πέλει ἡμιόνοιιν, τόσσον ὑπεκπροθέων</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:8:124\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">8.124</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>; later, simply, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">boundaries</tr_>, in pl., <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0001.tlg001.perseus-grc1:2:795\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ A.R.\">A.R.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">2.795</biblScope></bibl>.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}